snippet: The opposition leader Imran Khan and a cleric, Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri, rallied their supporters to demand that Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif resign.
abstract: Supporters of Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri gather on streets of Pakistan for protest march to demand the resignation of Prime Min Nawaz Sharif and fresh elections; timed to coincide with 67th anniversary of Pakistan's Independence, march follows weeks of growing political tension in the country and is strongest challenge yet to Sharif's 14-month-old government.

byline.contributor: Salman Masood contributed reporting from Islamabad, Pakistan, and Waqar Gillani from Lahore, Pakistan.

lead_paragraph: The opposition leader Imran Khan and a cleric, Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri, rallied their supporters to demand that Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif resign.

headline.main: Protest March Bears Down on the Leader of Pakistan
headline.print_headline: Protest March Bears Down on the Leader of Pakistan
